TY  - JOUR
AU  - Palacios-Huerta, Ignacio
T1  - Professionals Play Minimax
PY  - 2003
Y1  - 2003/04/01
DO  - 10.1111/1467-937X.00249
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 70
IS  - 2
SP  - 395
EP  - 415
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The implications of the Minimax theorem are tested using natural data. The tests use a unique data set from penalty kicks in professional soccer games. In this natural setting experts play a one-shot two-person zero-sum game. The results of the tests are remarkably consistent with equilibrium play in every respect: (i) winning probabilities are statistically identical across strategies for players; (ii) players' choices are serially independent. The tests have substantial power to distinguish equilibrium play from disequilibrium alternatives. These results represent the first time that both implications of von Neumann's Minimax theorem are supported under natural conditions.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00249
ER  - 



